Beating drums actually calls savages into existence.  (!)
	1-3 stacks, randomly
	in adjacent unoccupied provinces

Call wild men
	- constructs drum first if you don't have one
	- same as use <drum> 1
	- use drum 0 is a war challenge (!)


Describe savages in rules
	mention that they use a system of drumbeats to communicate
	covers call-to-arms, war challenge, and victory

victory in combat: fast beat

Ways of the wild men
Induce loyalty of wild men

Constructs a drum



if stacked under a savage,
	do nothing.

if in a structure,
	issue RAZE.

if there is an inn/castle/tower/ship/temple here,
{
	if empty,
		enter,
		issue RAZE.

	if human-occupied,
		beat drums to summon others,
		sav_wait,
		attack structure.
}

if a savage is beating drums nearby (or here),
	move to same location,
	stack under him.

unstack any savages beneath,
move randomly.

